ecc-aws-109-invalid_or_failed_certificat:
Checks an ACM for Invalid or Failed certificates. An Invalid certificate is the one that has not been validated within 72 hours. A certificate fails 'for these reasons:' 
- the certificate is requested for invalid public domains;
- the certificate is requested for domains which are not allowed or missing contact information;
- typographical errors.
These certificates cannot be used, and you will have to request new ones. It is recommended to delete Failed or Invalid certificates.

